body:
Yes, this is issue is similar to #710 but this problem seems to still be occurring.

I am using iverilog 12 and am attempting to run and compile the following simple System Verilog file, using the -g2012 standard.  However, when I run the resulting simulated vvp file, I get the same warning/error message as issue #710 of "VCD info: dumpfile test.vcd opened for output. VCD warning: $dumpvars: Package ($unit) is not dumpable with VCD." 

The aforementioned issue called it a warning message, but I also called it an error message because the resulting dumpfile of test.vcd is empty.   I've opened the vcd file in both gtkwave and vaporview, a vcd extension for vscode.  Both waveform viewers show that the dumped file is empty.

I tried running the exact same verilog code in Xilinx Vivado, and the waveform was generated properly.  The vcd output can be found here: https://bpa.st/R7EQ.  There does seem to be content within the file, so I am confused why the error message is displayed.

```
`timescale 1ns/1ns
module mod( input reg [7:0] op1, op2, input reg clock, output reg [7:0] out);
    always @(posedge clock) begin
        #1 out = op1 + op2;
    end
endmodule
module tb;
    reg [7:0] op1 = 'h0x1111;
    reg [7:0] op2 = 'h0x2222;
    reg [7:0] out;
    reg clock = 0;
    mod mod1(.op1(op1), .op2(op2), .out(out), .clock(clock));
    initial begin  
        $dumpfile("test.vcd");
        $dumpvars();
        $monitor("clock = %d, op1=0x%h8, op2=0x%h8, out = 0x%h8", clock, op1, op2, out);
        #30 $finish();        
    end
    always begin        
        #1 clock = ~clock; // posedge
        #1 op1 = op2 * 3;
        #1 clock = ~clock;
        #1 op2 = op1 - 2*op2;
        #1 clock = ~clock; // posedge
    end
endmodule
```

